cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this dataset, please cite both the dataset and the companion paper."
type: dataset
title: "RAITG: Requirement-Aware Intelligent Test Generator Dataset"
abstract: >-
  Dataset and reproducibility artefacts for the paper "AI-Driven Test Case
  Generation from Natural-Language Requirements: A Prompt-Engineered,
  Rule-Verified Framework for Scalable Software Quality Engineering". Includes
  312 natural-language requirements across commercial web, financial services,
  and healthcare domains; 936 per-requirement run logs produced on Anthropic
  Claude Sonnet 4.6 under three experimental conditions (unverified LLM,
  ablation without verification, full RAITG framework); aggregate and
  per-domain result CSVs; three reference applications used as mutation targets;
  the five-element prompt engineering taxonomy; the four-class rule-based
  verification calculus; and the end-to-end experimental pipeline.
authors:
